text:
Statistical meaning for linear model

Model: \(Y=X\beta+\varepsilon\), for \(\varepsilon\sim N(0,1)\)
Estimate \(\beta_0\), \(\beta_1\)

\[
Y = \begin{pmatrix}
Y_1\\
\vdots\\
Y_n
\end{pmatrix}
,\;
X = \begin{pmatrix}
1 & X_1\\
\vdots & \vdots\\
1 & X_n
\end{pmatrix}
,\;\text{and }\;
\beta = \begin{pmatrix}
\beta_0\\
\beta_1
\end{pmatrix}
\]

\(\hat{\beta} = \begin{pmatrix} \hat{\beta_0}\\ \hat{\beta_1} \end{pmatrix}\) is LSE of \(\beta\)
